climatePledgeFriendly.details: The Forest Stewardship Council certified products support responsible forestry, helping keep forests healthy for future generations.

features: A dry baby is a happy baby, and our Size 4 diapers provide the 12-hour protection that keeps those smiles coming.
The absorbent core in our diapers is not bleached or processed with chemicals containing chlorine, which prevents harmful toxins from entering waterways.
Our FreshAIR Breathable Layer helps release humidity and pulls moisture away from baby’s skin.
Made Free & Clear with 0% Fragrances, Lotions, or Chlorine Bleaching.
Made using only FSC Certified, sustainably harvested plant-based pulp, which helps nurture our planet’s forests.
body.description: Give your baby a clean, fresh start with Seventh Generation Diapers. Sensitive Protection for a happy today made from materials that nurture a healthy tomorrow. Our absorbent core provides the long-lasting, 12-hour protection that your busy baby needs, while our FreshAIR Breathable Layer helps release humidity. Our Free and Clear Diapers are made without fragrances, lotions, or chlorine bleaching, and use only FSC® Certified, sustainably sourced wood pulp that’s gentle on our planet’s forests. Wrapped in Seventh Generation’s softest, best diaper yet—the future looks good on your baby.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality and simply soft
reviews.reviewText: We love the original diapers. But these ones are so soft. I love that they did different designs for different sizes. Useful if you have two kids in diapers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ecofriendly and absorbent
reviews.reviewText: These are my favorite for eco friendly. They absorb better than huggies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Our Favorite Brand of Diapers
reviews.reviewText: I know these say they are for sensitive skin but I think all baby diapers should be made like this without dyes fragrance and extra things like chlorine bleaching. These things over time can cause issues so why even start with them!The best thing for the environment are cloth diapers but for convenience these are great and the company is working toward making things better so I'd rather support a company like Seventh Generation than some of the others.The diapers have good fit and leak guard. They are designed also to keep baby's skin dry to cut down on rashes.Overall these are great diapers.Thanks for reading my reviewBecky Brooks

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2021
reviews.reviewText: There's no scent which is awesome. The diapers with all the fishy had some dye bleed onto my kiddos legs, which I noticed while I changed him. It came right off, but not something I like to see happen. These are soft. They seem a little slim. He's a chunky boy and we're trying something else for the next month. But I do still like these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great upgraded diaper by seventh generation
reviews.reviewText: My daughter is 16m and we literally have tried most "natural/eco-friendly" diapers out there (naty, earth & eden, huggies special delivery, honest, and more) and also use cloth diapers.One of those diapers included the old version of seventh generation diapers which were not good (papery feel, non-existant hip straps, and subpar absorbancy)When I was given the opportunity to try these I was pleasantly surprised!I would say these are comparable to Huggies line of Special Delivery diapers. The diapers are very soft and stretchy which is great for adjusting it to different size thighs and bellies. The arent restricting at all and overall seem comfortable, so they will definitely be one of our top go-to brands of diapers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Work great for us
reviews.reviewText: I've been using these diapers for a few days and so far they have been great. My very active 14 month old is putting them to work while climbing, running, and rolling around; we haven't had an unfortunate mess yet. The diapers are super soft while still feeling like they will hold up. I like the stretch of the waistband and how secure the tabs are. Some diapers have tabs that get shifted out of place with a lot of scooting or flopping around, I haven't had that experience with these. There is no wetness indicator which I can of miss, but I will gladly give that up for the quality that these seem to be. I like that the lining that goes around the edge doesn't seem to irritate my kid's leg. We haven't had any blow outs or overnight leaks, so we are highly satisfied with these. My child sleeps through the entire night and if a diaper disaster compromised that I would be devastated.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I persoanlly am a huge fan of seventh generation brand. I had never tried the diaper line before receiving this box of size 4 diapers for my son. He is about 2 years old and this diaper fit him perfectly. The pattern is super cute as well. He sometimes has some sensitivities to diapers and wipes. He did not have any reaction to these specific seventh generation diapers so if thats a concern for your, you have nothing to worry about with these ones. The quantity was also very generous which I truly appreciate, I prefer these boxes of diapers instead of smaller quantities. Opening and closing the tabs are also easy and not complicated.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Work great; love the giant pack!
reviews.reviewText: These Seventh Generation diapers worked great. No leaks and fit my little guy just right. The design is cute. I love that they don't stink of fragrance. Nothing worse to me than deodorized stinky diaper changes. These diapers did not irritate my baby's skin. They have all the features of other premium diapers. Love the giant pack for longer times between ordering. Definitely recommended.
